<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD9FFD5FF58FC9F1600C01E" blockId="14.[144,758,785,838]" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FF58FC9F1646C07E" box="[144,269,785,806]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD9FFD5FE5AFC9C1541C07F" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[402,522,786,807]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FE5AFC9C1541C07F" box="[402,522,786,807]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is descriptive of the surstylar shape.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD9FFD5FF58FCFF164DC7AD" blockId="14.[144,759,880,1269]" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FF58FCFF161CC0DE" box="[144,343,881,902]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The male of species can be separated easily from other members of the Marginatum group by the male genitalia, yellow frons, and wings with brown basal area and dark cross veins. The larva and puparium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD9FFD5FE62FC65150CC758" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[426,583,1003,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FE62FC65150CC758" box="[426,583,1003,1024]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to other members of the Marginatum group in having the AP longer than the width of the TR. It is distinguished from all of these species except 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD9FFD5FD90FBC915BDC703" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1887" box="[600,758,1094,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipenne">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FD90FBC915BDC703" box="[600,758,1094,1116]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. limbipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the narrow band of spicules on the anterior fold and U-shaped arrangement of crochets on the mesothoracic prolegs. It is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD9FFD5FD46FB2C1799C78E" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipenne">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD9FFD5FD46FB2C1799C78E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. limbipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the nontapering AP which is about the width of the TR.
</paragraph>
